                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>\n                                        <date>Sept 3<hi rend=\"sup\">rd</hi> 5609</date>.</p>\n                              <p>My dear friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">In making my bow to you through the<lb/> medium of\n                                                  <persName>Miss DeCordova</persName>, the Bearer of\n                                        this letter, I beg you<lb/> not to bear hand upon me for not\n                                        visiting since my residence<lb/> here, having had enough to\n                                        occupy both my time and attention<lb/> in establishing a\n                                        school as a means of support, in which I<lb/> have been (I\n                                        E) tolerably successful. No doubt you expected<lb/> to hear\n                                        from me via <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>, but setting\n                                        aside my dislike of<lb/> the climate of that place, and the\n                                        repugnance of my wife to being<lb/> again separated from her\n                                        family, there are other reasons which<lb/> I may confide to\n                                        you, as a fellow labourer in the vineyard of<lb/> the Lord,\n                                        though to an <add>Hebrew</add> I would not reveal them.\n                                        They<lb/> are simply these. Having failed, despite my utmost\n                                        efforts, in<lb/> giving satisfaction to two congregations,\n                                                  <placeName>Kingston</placeName> &amp;\n                                                  <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>,<lb/> and,\n                                        instead of kind treatment, having been exposed to\n                                        insult<lb/> by both, I dread the idea of incurring it a\n                                        third time; and<lb/> therefore prefer the toilsome and\n                                        humble situation of a teacher<lb/> to the dignified one of a\n                                        Jewish minister. Perhaps my own<lb/> temper and disposition\n                                        are to blame; but, if so, is it not preferable<lb/> to\n                                        retire into private life and live in peace, than have them\n                                        again<lb/> excited by the <sic>disagreeabilities</sic> of a\n                                        Jewish Congregation?<lb/> In <placeName>St.\n                                                  Thomas</placeName>, I even offered to serve them\n                                        gratuitously, as<lb/> salary was the bone of contention\n                                        among the members, provided<lb/> they would be at peace with\n                                        each other. This, the party in power<lb/> would not suffer;\n                                        and subsequently I accepted a very trifling</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3891271d/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
